It is possible to define assortments for customer hierarchy levels.

<img width="" src="https://docs.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000604-0/img17.png"><br>

It is also possible to define the control constraint of the assortment.

<img width="" src="https://docs.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000604-0/img18.png"><br>

* Constraint: the system blocks if the item is not present in the assortment

<img width="" src="https://docs.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000604-0/Immagine19.png"><br>

* Constraint with confirmation: the system returns an alert message but allows the insertion of an out-of-assortment item in the order

<img width="" src="https://docs.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000604-0/Immagine20.png"><br>

* No Constraint: The system places no constraint on the insertion of an out-of-assortment item